CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, page 16, reads: "2. Huge crowds filled every inch of available space in the exhibit hall"
TitMainTitle: Crowd of men, and women, including one standing on right wearing dark hat and dark dress with light colored collar, gathered in front of banner that reads "Crosley and Bendix Home Appliances Divisions", at Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair, Syria Mosque
